---
// The project's primary demoable artifact: upload a real fitness-app export, watch it get
// parsed into portable OpenBody JSON, entirely client-side. No file ever leaves the browser.
//
// This is a custom Astro page (outside the `docs` content collection) rather than an .mdx
// page, because it needs real interactivity (file upload, in-browser parsing, a client-side
// download) — Starlight's content collection is markdown/static. `StarlightPage` gives it the
// same header/sidebar/theme chrome as the rest of the site while letting the body be
// hand-written HTML + a vanilla client-side `<script>` (no UI framework needed or installed).
//
// Parsing uses the real @openbody/openbody-ts package directly (mapHevy, mapStrong,
// mapAppleHealth, mapStrava) — no vendored copy needed: openbody-ts's validate.ts no
// longer pulls in node:fs/path/url at module load, so the package is safe to import from
// browser-bundled code. Source detection + the thin activities.csv → mapStrava adapter
// live in src/components/convert-sources.ts.
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
import { Aside } from "@astrojs/starlight/components";
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: "Convert your workout data",
    description:
      "Upload a Hevy, Strong, Apple Health, or Strava export and see it parsed into portable OpenBody JSON, entirely in your browser. No signup, no server, no upload.",
    tableOfContents: false,
  }}
>
  <p><span class="ob-status">EXPERIMENTAL · pre-v1.0 tool</span></p>

  <p class="ob-lede">
    Your workout history is stuck in whatever app you logged it in. This is a small demo of
    what OpenBody is for: pick a real export from a fitness app, watch it parsed into a
    portable, human-readable record in your own browser, and download the result. Nothing is
    uploaded anywhere — the parsing code runs on your machine, not a server.
  </p>

  <Aside type="caution" title="Early, experimental">
    OpenBody itself is a <strong>pre-v1.0 draft standard</strong> (see the
    <a href="/specification/">specification</a>), and this converter is a demo tool, not a
    finished product. It reads the four export formats below via the reference mappers in
    <a href="https://github.com/openbody/openbody-ts">openbody-ts</a>; each card says
    exactly what is and isn't read. More formats (FIT files, per-activity GPX) are planned;
    see the <a href="/mapping/">mapping guides</a> for the mappings that exist in the
    reference implementation.
  </Aside>

  <h2>Supported exports</h2>
  <div class="ob-source-grid">
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Hevy — workout CSV</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">Hevy app → Profile → Settings → Export Data.</p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Full lifting history: workouts, exercises, sets, reps, load, RPE, supersets.
        Exercise names are matched to canonical OpenBody movements where known.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Strong — workout CSV</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">Strong app → Profile → Settings → Export Strong Data.</p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Workouts, exercises, sets, weight, reps, plus distance/time sets. Same canonical
        exercise matching as Hevy.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Apple Health — export.xml</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">
        Health app → profile picture → Export All Health Data, then <strong>unzip</strong>
        the export.zip and pick <code>export.xml</code>.
      </p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Workouts become sessions (duration, distance, energy); heart rate, step count, body
        mass, and sleep-stage records become measurements. Per-workout GPS routes and other
        record types aren't read yet. Big exports can take a moment — it all runs locally.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ob-source-card">
      <p class="ob-source-name">Strava — activities.csv</p>
      <p class="ob-source-how">
        strava.com → Settings → My Account → Download or Delete Your Account → Download
        Request, then pick <code>activities.csv</code> from the archive.
      </p>
      <p class="ob-source-what">
        Summary per activity only: sport, date, moving/elapsed time, distance. The GPS,
        heart-rate, and power streams (the GPX/FIT files in the same archive) are coming
        later.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Export your data from one of the apps above.</li>
    <li>Drop the file below — the format is detected automatically. Parsing happens entirely
      in your browser via JavaScript — the file is never sent anywhere.</li>
    <li>Review the human-readable preview, then download the portable OpenBody JSON.</li>
  </ol>

  <div id="convert-tool" class="ob-tool">
    <label id="drop-zone" for="file-input" class="ob-dropzone">
      <input id="file-input" type="file" accept=".csv,.xml,text/csv,text/xml,application/xml" />
      <span class="ob-dropzone-title">Choose an export file, or drag it here</span>
      <span class="ob-dropzone-sub">Hevy CSV · Strong CSV · Apple Health export.xml · Strava activities.csv</span>
      <span class="ob-dropzone-sub">Nothing is uploaded — parsing happens in your browser.</span>
    </label>

    <p id="status" class="ob-status-msg" role="status" aria-live="polite" hidden></p>

    <div id="resolution" class="ob-resolution" hidden></div>

    <div id="preview" class="ob-preview" hidden></div>

    <button id="download-btn" type="button" class="ob-btn ob-btn-primary" hidden>
      Download as OpenBody JSON
    </button>

    <div id="email-capture" class="ob-email-card" hidden>
      <form id="email-form">
        <p class="ob-email-title">Want to know when more apps are supported?</p>
        <p class="ob-email-sub">
          Optional — totally skippable. We'll only email about new source formats for this
          tool and major OpenBody milestones.
        </p>
        <div class="ob-email-row">
          <input
            id="email-input"
            type="email"
            name="email"
            placeholder="you@example.com"
            required
            aria-label="Email address"
          />
          <button type="submit" class="ob-btn ob-btn-secondary">Notify me</button>
          <button id="email-dismiss" type="button" class="ob-btn ob-btn-ghost">No thanks</button>
        </div>
        <p id="email-status" class="ob-email-status" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What is "OpenBody JSON"?</h2>
  <p>
    The downloaded file is an array of OpenBody records — <code>Session</code> records for
    workouts, plus <code>Measurement</code> records for Apple Health data like heart rate
    and sleep stages. It's the same wire format documented in the
    <a href="/mapping/">mapping guides</a> and validated against the
    <a href="/specification/schema/">JSON Schema</a>: a plain, inspectable JSON file you
    own. Move it between tools, check it into your own backup, or feed it to anything else
    that speaks OpenBody.
  </p>

  <script>
    import { mapHevy, mapStrong, mapAppleHealth } from "@openbody/openbody-ts";
    import { summarizeSessions, formatSetLine, type SessionSummary } from "../../lib/hevy/summarize";
    import {
      detectSource,
      mapStravaActivitiesCsv,
      summarizeEndurance,
      formatDuration,
      SOURCE_LABEL,
      SOURCE_KIND,
      type SourceId,
    } from "../../components/convert-sources";

    const fileInput = document.getElementById("file-input") as HTMLInputElement;
    const dropZone = document.getElementById("drop-zone") as HTMLElement;
    const statusEl = document.getElementById("status") as HTMLElement;
    const resolutionEl = document.getElementById("resolution") as HTMLElement;
    const previewEl = document.getElementById("preview") as HTMLElement;
    const downloadBtn = document.getElementById("download-btn") as HTMLButtonElement;
    const emailCapture = document.getElementById("email-capture") as HTMLElement;
    const emailForm = document.getElementById("email-form") as HTMLFormElement;
    const emailInput = document.getElementById("email-input") as HTMLInputElement;
    const emailStatus = document.getElementById("email-status") as HTMLElement;
    const emailDismiss = document.getElementById("email-dismiss") as HTMLButtonElement;

    let lastRecords: unknown[] | null = null;
    let lastBaseName = "openbody-export";

    function setStatus(message: string, kind: "info" | "success" | "error") {
      statusEl.hidden = false;
      statusEl.textContent = message;
      statusEl.className = `ob-status-msg is-${kind}`;
    }

    function resetPreview() {
      previewEl.hidden = true;
      previewEl.replaceChildren();
      resolutionEl.hidden = true;
      resolutionEl.replaceChildren();
      downloadBtn.hidden = true;
      lastRecords = null;
    }

    // Exercise-identity resolution summary (SPEC §6): the mappers now climb the matching
    // ladder via the canonical registry crosswalk, so each Exercise's `exerciseRef` carries
    // a canonical `id` when the app's exercise name is a known movement, and always keeps
    // the original name losslessly (`opaque`). This runs on the already-mapped records —
    // still 100% client-side, nothing leaves the browser.
    function renderResolution(records: any[]) {
      const refs: { name: string; id?: string }[] = [];
      const seen = new Set<string>();
      for (const session of records) {
        const exercises = [
          ...(session.exercises ?? []),
          ...((session.blocks ?? []).flatMap((b: any) => b.children ?? [])),
        ];
        for (const ex of exercises) {
          const er = ex?.exerciseRef;
          if (er === undefined) continue;
          const id = typeof er === "string" ? er : er.id;
          const name = (typeof er === "string" ? undefined : er.opaque) ?? id ?? "(unnamed)";
          if (seen.has(name)) continue;
          seen.add(name);
          refs.push({ name, id });
        }
      }
      if (refs.length === 0) return;

      const resolved = refs.filter((r) => r.id !== undefined).length;
      const title = document.createElement("p");
      title.className = "ob-resolution-title";
      title.textContent =
        `${resolved} of ${refs.length} exercises recognized as canonical OpenBody movements` +
        ` — the rest are kept as-is (lossless).`;

      const list = document.createElement("ul");
      list.className = "ob-resolution-list";
      for (const r of refs) {
        const li = document.createElement("li");
        const nameEl = document.createElement("span");
        nameEl.className = "ob-resolution-name";
        nameEl.textContent = r.name;
        li.append(nameEl);
        if (r.id !== undefined) {
          li.append(" → ");
          const idEl = document.createElement("code");
          idEl.textContent = r.id;
          li.append(idEl);
        } else {
          const keptEl = document.createElement("span");
          keptEl.className = "ob-resolution-kept";
          keptEl.textContent = " — kept as-is (lossless)";
          li.append(keptEl);
        }
        list.append(li);
      }
      resolutionEl.replaceChildren(title, list);
      resolutionEl.hidden = false;
    }

    function renderPreview(records: unknown[]) {
      const sessions: SessionSummary[] = summarizeSessions(records as any);
      previewEl.replaceChildren();

      if (sessions.length === 0) {
        const p = document.createElement("p");
        p.textContent = "No sessions parsed from that file.";
        previewEl.append(p);
      }

      for (const session of sessions) {
        const card = document.createElement("article");
        card.className = "ob-session-card";

        const heading = document.createElement("h3");
        heading.textContent = session.name;
        const dateEl = document.createElement("p");
        dateEl.className = "ob-session-date";
        dateEl.textContent = session.dateLabel;
        card.append(heading, dateEl);

        const exList = document.createElement("div");
        exList.className = "ob-exercise-list";
        for (const ex of session.exercises) {
          const exBlock = document.createElement("div");
          exBlock.className = "ob-exercise";

          const exName = document.createElement("p");
          exName.className = "ob-exercise-name";
          exName.textContent = ex.supersetGroup ? `${ex.name} (superset)` : ex.name;
          exBlock.append(exName);

          const setList = document.createElement("ul");
          setList.className = "ob-set-list";
          for (const set of ex.sets) {
            const li = document.createElement("li");
            li.textContent = `Set ${set.index}: ${formatSetLine(set)}`;
            setList.append(li);
          }
          exBlock.append(setList);
          exList.append(exBlock);
        }
        card.append(exList);
        previewEl.append(card);
      }

      previewEl.hidden = false;
    }

    // Endurance sources (Apple Health, Strava) don't have sets/reps to preview or exercise
    // names to resolve — show a sessions/disciplines/totals rollup instead, plus per-session
    // cards. Still 100% client-side.
    const ENDURANCE_PREVIEW_CAP = 50;
    function renderEnduranceSummary(records: any[]) {
      const summary = summarizeEndurance(records);

      const title = document.createElement("p");
      title.className = "ob-resolution-title";
      const bits: string[] = [`${summary.sessionCount} session${summary.sessionCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}`];
      if (summary.totalKm > 0) bits.push(`${summary.totalKm.toFixed(summary.totalKm >= 100 ? 0 : 1)} km`);
      if (summary.totalSeconds > 0) bits.push(formatDuration(summary.totalSeconds));
      title.textContent = bits.join(" · ");

      const list = document.createElement("ul");
      list.className = "ob-resolution-list";
      if (summary.disciplines.length > 0) {
        const li = document.createElement("li");
        li.textContent =
          "Disciplines: " + summary.disciplines.map(([d, n]) => `${d} ×${n}`).join(", ");
        list.append(li);
      }
      if (summary.measurementCount > 0) {
        const li = document.createElement("li");
        li.textContent =
          `${summary.measurementCount} measurement${summary.measurementCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}: ` +
          summary.measurementsByType.map(([t, n]) => `${t} ×${n}`).join(", ");
        list.append(li);
      }
      resolutionEl.replaceChildren(title, ...(list.childElementCount ? [list] : []));
      resolutionEl.hidden = false;

      previewEl.replaceChildren();
      for (const session of summary.sessions.slice(0, ENDURANCE_PREVIEW_CAP)) {
        const card = document.createElement("article");
        card.className = "ob-session-card";
        const heading = document.createElement("h3");
        heading.textContent = session.name;
        const dateEl = document.createElement("p");
        dateEl.className = "ob-session-date";
        dateEl.textContent = session.dateLabel;
        const partsEl = document.createElement("p");
        partsEl.className = "ob-session-parts";
        partsEl.textContent = session.parts.join(" · ");
        card.append(heading, dateEl, partsEl);
        previewEl.append(card);
      }
      if (summary.sessions.length > ENDURANCE_PREVIEW_CAP) {
        const more = document.createElement("p");
        more.className = "ob-preview-more";
        more.textContent =
          `…and ${summary.sessions.length - ENDURANCE_PREVIEW_CAP} more sessions ` +
          `(all included in the download).`;
        previewEl.append(more);
      }
      previewEl.hidden = false;
    }

    const SUPPORTED_HINT =
      "Supported: Hevy CSV, Strong CSV, Apple Health export.xml, Strava activities.csv.";

    function mapForSource(source: SourceId, text: string) {
      switch (source) {
        case "hevy": return mapHevy(text);
        case "strong": return mapStrong(text);
        case "apple-health": return mapAppleHealth(text);
        case "strava": return mapStravaActivitiesCsv(text);
      }
    }

    async function handleFile(file: File) {
      resetPreview();
      emailCapture.hidden = true;
      setStatus(`Reading ${file.name}…`, "info");
      try {
        // ZIP (Apple Health export.zip, Strava archive) — ask for the inner file instead of
        // shipping an unzip library to the browser.
        const magic = new Uint8Array(await file.slice(0, 2).arrayBuffer());
        if (magic[0] === 0x50 && magic[1] === 0x4b) {
          setStatus(
            "That's a ZIP archive. Unzip it first, then drop the file inside: export.xml " +
              "for Apple Health, activities.csv for Strava.",
            "error",
          );
          return;
        }

        const text = await file.text();
        const source = detectSource(file.name, text);
        if (!source) {
          setStatus(`Couldn't recognize that file as a supported export. ${SUPPORTED_HINT}`, "error");
          return;
        }
        setStatus(`Detected ${SOURCE_LABEL[source]} — parsing…`, "info");

        const records = mapForSource(source, text);
        const sessionCount = records.filter((r: any) => r.recordType === "Session").length;
        if (!records.length || (SOURCE_KIND[source] === "strength" && sessionCount === 0)) {
          setStatus(
            `No workouts found in that file — is it an unmodified ${SOURCE_LABEL[source]} export?`,
            "error",
          );
          return;
        }
        lastRecords = records;
        lastBaseName = file.name.replace(/\.(csv|xml)$/i, "") || "openbody-export";

        if (SOURCE_KIND[source] === "strength") {
          renderResolution(records);
          renderPreview(records);
        } else {
          renderEnduranceSummary(records);
        }

        const measurementCount = records.length - sessionCount;
        const parsedBits = [`${sessionCount} session${sessionCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}`];
        if (measurementCount > 0) {
          parsedBits.push(`${measurementCount} measurement${measurementCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}`);
        }
        setStatus(
          `${SOURCE_LABEL[source]}: parsed ${parsedBits.join(" and ")} from ${file.name}. ` +
            `Nothing left your browser.`,
          "success",
        );
        downloadBtn.hidden = false;
        emailCapture.hidden = false;
      } catch (err) {
        console.error("[convert-tool] parse failed:", err);
        setStatus(
          `Couldn't parse that file (${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}). ` +
            `Make sure it's an unmodified export. ${SUPPORTED_HINT}`,
          "error",
        );
      }
    }

    fileInput?.addEventListener("change", () => {
      const file = fileInput.files?.[0];
      if (file) void handleFile(file);
    });

    dropZone?.addEventListener("dragover", (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      dropZone.classList.add("is-dragover");
    });
    for (const evt of ["dragleave", "drop"]) {
      dropZone?.addEventListener(evt, () => dropZone.classList.remove("is-dragover"));
    }
    dropZone?.addEventListener("drop", (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const file = e.dataTransfer?.files?.[0];
      if (file) void handleFile(file);
    });

    downloadBtn?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      if (!lastRecords) return;
      const blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(lastRecords, null, 2)], { type: "application/json" });
      const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
      const a = document.createElement("a");
      a.href = url;
      a.download = `${lastBaseName}.openbody.json`;
      document.body.append(a);
      a.click();
      a.remove();
      URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
    });

    emailDismiss?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      emailCapture.hidden = true;
    });

    emailForm?.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const email = emailInput.value.trim();
      if (!email) return;
      const submitBtn = emailForm.querySelector("button[type=submit]") as HTMLButtonElement;
      submitBtn.disabled = true;
      emailStatus.textContent = "Sending…";
      emailStatus.className = "ob-email-status";
      try {
        // TODO(backend): /api/subscribe is a PLACEHOLDER. There is no server behind this yet —
        // this site builds as static output for Cloudflare Pages, with no Worker / Pages
        // Function / KV / D1 wired up. Implementing it is a founder-level decision (which
        // mechanism, retention, unsubscribe, etc.), not something to fake here. Until it
        // exists this request will fail (404), and we surface that honestly below instead of
        // showing a fake success state.
        const res = await fetch("/api/subscribe", {
          method: "POST",
          headers: { "content-type": "application/json" },
          body: JSON.stringify({ email, source: "convert-tool" }),
        });
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`);
        emailStatus.textContent = "Thanks — we'll let you know.";
        emailStatus.className = "ob-email-status is-success";
        emailForm.hidden = true;
      } catch (err) {
        console.warn("[convert-tool] /api/subscribe isn't wired up yet:", err);
        emailStatus.textContent =
          "Thanks for the interest — signups aren't actually wired up in this early version, " +
          "so this didn't go anywhere yet. Check back soon.";
        emailStatus.className = "ob-email-status is-pending";
      } finally {
        submitBtn.disabled = false;
      }
    });
  </script>

  <style>
    .ob-lede {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .ob-tool {
      margin: 2rem 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .ob-source-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .ob-source-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-source-name {
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-source-how {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-source-what {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }

    .ob-dropzone {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.35rem;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
      border: 2px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .ob-dropzone:hover,
    .ob-dropzone.is-dragover {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 6%, transparent);
    }
    .ob-dropzone input[type="file"] {
      position: absolute;
      width: 1px;
      height: 1px;
      opacity: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ob-dropzone-title {
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-dropzone-sub {
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    .ob-status-msg {
      font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 0.35rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-info {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-4);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-success {
      border-color: var(--sl-color-accent);
      color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
      background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent) 8%, transparent);
    }
    .ob-status-msg.is-error {
      border-color: #b3261e;
      color: #b3261e;
    }

    .ob-resolution {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-resolution-title {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-resolution-list {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-resolution-name {
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .ob-resolution-kept {
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }

    .ob-preview {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .ob-session-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-bg-nav);
    }
    .ob-session-card h3 {
      margin: 0;
    }
    .ob-session-date {
      margin: 0.15rem 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    }
    .ob-session-parts {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    }
    .ob-preview-more {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
      color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .ob-exercise-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }
    .ob-exercise-name {
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    }
    .ob-set-list {
      margin: 0;
